    <statement>
        <p>
Use technology to complete the following table of values.
<me>f(x)=\frac{ x^{2} - x - 42 }{ x^{2} - 10 \, x + 21 }</me>
            <me>
\begin{array}{c|ccccccc}
x &amp; 6.9&amp; 6.99&amp; 6.999&amp; 7&amp; 7.001&amp; 7.01&amp; 7.1 \\\hline
f(x) &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp;  \\
\end{array}
            </me>
        </p>
        <p>
Then explain how to use it to make an educated guess as to the value of
the limit <me>\lim_{ x\to 7 } \frac{ x^{2} - x - 42 }{ x^{2} - 10 \, x + 21 }</me>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <me>
\begin{array}{c|ccccccc}
x &amp; 6.9&amp; 6.99&amp; 6.999&amp; 7&amp; 7.001&amp; 7.01&amp; 7.1 \\\hline
f(x) &amp; 3.30769&amp; 3.25564&amp; 3.25056&amp; DNE&amp; 3.24944&amp; 3.24439&amp; 3.19512 \\
\end{array}
            </me>
        </p>
        <p>
The limit is <m>3.25</m>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
